import express from 'express'
import dotenv from 'dotenv'
import http from 'http'
import WebSocket from 'ws'
import bodyParser from 'body-parser'

import routes from './routes'

dotenv.config()
const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3030

const app = express()
const server = http.createServer(app)
const wss = new WebSocket.Server({ server })

app.use(bodyParser.json())

wss.on('connection', (ws) => {})

app.use('/api', routes)

server.listen(PORT, () => console.log(`Server is listening on port ${PORT}`))

import express from 'express'

import game from './game'

const router = express.Router()

router.use('/game', game)

export default router

import express from 'express'
import shortId from 'shortid'
import Joi from 'joi'
import { values } from 'lodash'

import { Game } from '../constant'

const router = express.Router()

router.post('/create', (req, res) => {
	const schema = Joi.object({
		name: Joi.string().alphanum().min(3).max(100).required().message('Game name is missing'),
		system: Joi.number()
			.valid(values(...Game.System))
			.required()
			.message('Voting system is missing'),
		show: Joi.number()
			.valid(values(...Game.Show))
			.required()
			.message('Who can show cards is missing'),
	})

	const validation = schema.valid(req.body)
	console.log(validation)

	const gameId = shortId.generate()
	console.log(gameId)
	res.sendStatus(201)
})

export default router

import express from 'express'
import shortId from 'shortid'
import Joi from 'joi'
import { values } from 'lodash'

import { Game } from '../constant'
import { codes } from '../errorCode'
import { DAL } from '../db'

const router = express.Router()

router.post('/create', (req, res) => {
	const schema = Joi.object({
		name: Joi.string().alphanum().min(3).max(100).required(),
		player: Joi.string().alphanum().min(3).max(100).required(),
		system: Joi.number()
			.valid(...values(Game.System))
			.required(),
		show: Joi.number()
			.valid(...values(Game.Show))
			.required(),
	})

	const validation = schema.validate(req.body)
	if (validation.error) {
		res.status(400).json(codes.create.requestValidation(400))
	}

	const gameId = shortId.generate()
	const sessionId = '1'
	const { player: playerName, show: canShow } = req.body
	DAL.addPlayer(gameId, playerName, sessionId)
	DAL.canShow(gameId, canShow)
	res.sendStatus(201)
})

export default router
